author: Jacob Gallant
title: Memphis defeats Ole Miss 37-24
text:
Memphis defeats Ole Miss 37-24 - WMC Action News 5 - Memphis, Tennessee Member Center: Memphis defeats Ole Miss 37-24 Posted: (Source: WMC Action News 5) MEMPHIS, TN (WMC) - 
The Memphis Tigers defeated Ole Miss 37-24. 
After the Rebels jumped out to a 14-0 first quarter lead, the Tigers pounced back with 31 unanswered. 
The game shifted when Ole Miss used star defensive tackle Robert Knemdiche on offense in the second quarter. Knemdiche failed to convert on third down and would not return to the game. Ole Miss failed to convert once again on fourth down, and Memphis took over on offense. 
Tigersâ€™ quarterback Paxton Lynch backed the Tigers with a huge game, completing 39 of his 53 passes for 384 yards and three touchdowns. 
The Ole Miss defense struggled to contain the Tigers offense all day, with Memphis scoring 31 unanswered points. Ole Miss clawed back to make it a 31-24 game, but could not ever regain their lead in front of the packed Liberty Bowl.
